reviews.review_text: first to review is always weird espcially when it sounds damn good, performence is not out of this world neither is the setlist but it is an all around good show with a very good throwing stones,

I need to rant a little sorry bigboypeete, I took your name.  Just want to express my absolute disgust with the no sbd download policy.  Haven't we heads been through enough heartache?  Now they want to take away access to the best sounding memories that we need to keep the faith.  I don't know the particulars of the whole thing but to whomever could have stopped this travesty I hope it all comkes back to bite you in the ass.  I'm gonna record the streaming format of this just out of spite and because it is a good show.
9-6-88 Good show. Good sbd by Charlie. A little crowd noise mixed in almost makes me feel like I was there.
